          <lg n="1">
            <l xml:id="swift-430-1301-line-1" n="1"><hi rend="display-initial">U</hi>N<hi rend="small-caps">DER</hi> this stone lie Dicky and Dolly;</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-430-1301-line-2" n="2">Doll dying first, Dick grew melancholy;</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-430-1301-line-3" n="3">For Dick without Doll thought living a folly.</l>
            <l rend="indent(1)" xml:id="swift-430-1301-line-4" n="4"><lb/>Dick lost in Doll a wife tender and dear,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-430-1301-line-5" n="5">But Dick lost by Doll twelve hundred a year;</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-430-1301-line-6" n="6">A loss that Dick thought no mortal could bear.</l>
            <l rend="indent(1)" xml:id="swift-430-1301-line-7" n="7"><lb/>Dick sigh'd for his Doll, and his mournful arms crost;</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-430-1301-line-8" n="8">Thought much of his Doll, and the jointure he lost:</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-430-1301-line-9" n="9">The first vex'd him much, the other vex'd most.</l>
            <l rend="indent(1)" xml:id="swift-430-1301-line-10" n="10"><lb/>Thus loaded with grief, Dick sigh'd and he cry'd;</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-430-1301-line-11" n="11">To live without both full three days he try'd:</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-430-1301-line-12" n="12">But lik'd neither loss, and so quietly dy'd.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-430-1301-line-13" n="13">om.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-430-1301-line-14" n="14">om.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-430-1301-line-15" n="15">om.</l>
            <l rend="indent(1)" xml:id="swift-430-1301-line-16" n="16"><lb/>Dick left a pattern few will copy after:</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-430-1301-line-17" n="17">Then, reader, pray shed some tears of salt water;</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-430-1301-line-18" n="18">For so sad a tale is no subject of laughter.</l>
            <l rend="indent(1)" xml:id="swift-430-1301-line-19" n="19"><lb/>M──th smiles for the jointure, tho' gotten so late;</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-430-1301-line-20" n="20">The son laughs that got the hard-gotten estate;</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-430-1301-line-21" n="21">And <note place="foot">·General G──ges's son-in-law.</note> Cuff grins, for getting the Alicant plate.</l>
            <l rend="indent(1)" xml:id="swift-430-1301-line-22" n="22"><lb/>Here quiet they lie, in hopes to rise one day,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-430-1301-line-23" n="23">Both solemnly put in this hole on a Sunday,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-430-1301-line-24" n="24">And here rest; <hi rend="italics">sic transit gloria mundi</hi>.</l>
          </lg>
